: false, "description": "Area: compiler plugins, doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/unstable-book/language-features/plugin.html"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2016-01-21T03:04:44Z", "updated_at": "2016-01-25T12:29:15Z", "closed_at": "2016-01-25T12:29:15Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Started occurring after https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/f9d4149c29e8b989fa3624993be379f380e48dcf merged\n\n---\n\n[Repo exemplifying segfault](https://github.com/frewsxcv/rust-llvm-pass-segfault)\n\n[Relevant file in repo](https://github.com/frewsxcv/rust-llvm-pass-segfault/blob/master/some_plugin/src/llvm-pass.cc)\n\nTo exemplify:\n1. set `LLVM_CONFIG` environment variable to `llvm-config` path\n2. `cargo build --verbose`\n\n[Result of stepping through the code with LLDB](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/frewsxcv/d60b0e08945f8a592a7d/raw/5b78260cc740cac3719d0a9e8abc98991ec53ec6/gistfile1.txt)\n\n---\n\nAnother example of a module pass exemplifying a crash:\n\n``` cpp\nbool InstrumentationPass::runOnModule(Module &M) {\n  LLVMContext &C = M.getContext();\n  IntegerType *Int8Ty  = IntegerType::getInt8Ty(C);\n  llvm::Type *i = PointerType::get(Int8Ty, 0);  // segfault happens here\n  return true;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nThis is preventing [afl.rs](https://github.com/frewsxcv/afl.rs) from upgrading compatibility with any Rust version >1.2:\n- https://github.com/frewsxcv/afl.rs/issues/11\n", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https